articlebody:
It's time for one of central Ohio's favorite Easter-time traditions: the 15th annual edition of Joe's Mildly Entertaining Easter Egg Hunt.
Through April 7, I will present 10 rhyming riddles -- one per day -- containing clues to the location of imaginary eggs.
The locations can be landmarks, businesses, artwork, cultural attractions or other spots, some more prominent than others.
As each riddle is released, it will appear with the others at the bottom of this page.
>> To view all of the clues visit: Dispatch.com/easter2020
